Preconditions:
- The input array "parent" is not null.
- The input array "parent" has at least one element.
- The input string "s" is not null.
- The input string "s" is not empty.
- The length of the input string "s" is equal to the length of the input array "parent".

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer value.
- The returned integer value represents the length of the longest path in the tree.
- The longest path in the tree has the property that no pair of adjacent nodes on the path have the same character assigned to them.